{{Spanish name|Sánchez|Piñol}} {{Infobox writer | name = Albert Sánchez Piñol | image = Albert Sánchez Piñol, Göteborg Book Fair 2014 2 (crop).jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1965}}<!-- {{Birth date and age|Year|Month|Day}} --> | birth_place = [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Spain | occupation = [[Anthropologist]] and writer | ethnicity = | citizenship = [[Spaniard|Spanish]] | alma_mater = | period = 20th&ndash;21st centuries | genre = Non-fiction and novels | subject = | movement = | notableworks = | spouse = | partner = | children = | relatives = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | website = | portaldisp = }}
'''Albert Sánchez Piñol''' ({{IPA-es|əlˈβɛrt ˈsaɲtʃeθ piˈɲɔl}}; born 1965 in [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Spain) is a [[Spaniard|Spanish]] [[anthropologist]], non-fiction writer and novelist writing in [[Catalan language|Catalan]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]].
He has been described as a "significant European writer".<ref>[[Giles Foden|Foden, Giles]] (25 April 2008). [https://www.theguardian.com/books/2008/apr/26/featuresreviews.guardianreview30 "Art of Darkness{{spaced ndash}}Giles Foden Enjoys Albert Sánchez Piñol's Genre-Busting Expedition into the Heart of Colonial Africa, Pandora in the Congo"]. ''[[The Guardian]]''. Retrieved 10 February 2012.</ref><ref>Eaude, Michael (16 May 2008). [https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/reviews/pandora-in-the-congo-by-albert-s225nchez-pi241ol-trans-mara-faye-lethem-828945.html "Pandora in the Congo, by Albert Sánchez Piñol, trans. Mara Faye Lethem{{spaced ndash}}A Book of Dangerous Boys"]. ''[[The Independent]]''. Retrieved 10 February 2012.</ref><ref>[[Marcel Theroux|Theroux, Marcel]] (19 December 2005). [https://www.nytimes.com/2005/12/18/arts/18iht-bookmon.html "Cold Skin"]. ''[[The New York Times]]''. Retrieved 10 February 2012.</ref>
