{{Infobox language |name=Somra |nativename=Tangkhul |states=[[Burma]] |ethnicity=[[Tangkhul Naga]] |speakers=4,000 |date=2004 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Tangkhulic languages|Tangkhulic]] |dia1=Somra |iso3=ntx |glotto=none }}
'''Somra''' (after its literary dialect), also known as '''Burmese Tangkhul''' (Tangkhul Naga), is a [[Sino-Tibetan languages|Sino-Tibetan]] language spoken in Burma. The two ethnic Tangkhul languages are related, but are not mutually intelligible, being only 30% lexically similar.<ref name=e18/> Somra is closer to [[Akyaung Ari language|Akyaung Ari]].
Somra is spoken in Somra tract, [[Leshi Township]] and [[Homalin Township]] of [[Sagaing Division]], Myanmar.
